field.value:
Right now Windsor's default release policy will track a component if any of its dependencies has decommission concerns. This is sometimes superfluous, for example:

{code lang=java}
[Transient]
public class A
{
   public B Dependency {get; set;}
}

[Singleton]
public class B: IDisposable
{
   public void Dispose()
   {
   }
}

{code}


In this case when we resolve A, it will be tracked although no action will be taken when we release it, so it would be safe not to track it at all.
This obviously can be extended to other kinds of interdependencies, not just transient --> singleton, but to non-scoped (transient/pooled) -> scoped (per-web-request/per-thread/singleton). Don't know how to handle custom lifestyles here yet. We might introduce {{IScopedLifestyle}} or something to make that explicit. Ideas are welcome.
